The Hawks have arrested a 39-year-old suspect in connection with the murder of anti-gang unit investigator, Charl Kinnear. The suspect was arrested in Gauteng on Wednesday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks say they believe more people may be involved in the murder of the anti-gang unit investigator, Charl Kinnear. Kinnear was gunned down outside his house last week. One suspect has been arrested and will appear in court on Friday. READ: R1m reward for info leading to arrest of Kinnear killers The Hawks say they are focusing on making more arrests. "There is a lot that needs to be done, we have information that we have already gathered, we are expecting more arrests," said Hawks spokespersonÂ Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi.